According to [the documentation][1], use a relative path for a local jar dependency as follows.

Groovy syntax:

    dependencies {
        implementation files(&#39;libs/something_local.jar&#39;)
    }

Kotlin syntax:

    dependencies {
        implementation(files(&quot;libs/something_local.jar&quot;))
    }


  [1]: https://docs.gradle.org/5.2.1/userguide/dependency_types.html#sub:file_dependencies

You could also do this which would include all JARs in the local repository.  This way you wouldn&#39;t have to specify it every time.

    dependencies {
        compile fileTree(dir: &#39;libs&#39;, include: [&#39;*.jar&#39;])
    }

